This is a list of some of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūku Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|12=draft}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]]. This article covers the shrines in the regions of Kaizuka.
==Overview== {{Shrine | Name = {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft}} | image = | location = {{ill|Kishiwada, Osaka|ja|岸和田市|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kaizuka, Osaka|ja|貝塚市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|12=draft}}, Japan | coordinates = | deity = | Affiliation = {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft}} - {{ill|Kumano Pilgrimage|ja|熊野信仰|1=Kumano Three Shrines|lt=Kumano faith|12=draft}} | Established = | Map = }}
This article covers the '''{{ill|Kujūku Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft}}''' shrines located within {{ill|Kishiwada, Osaka|ja|岸和田市|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kaizuka, Osaka|ja|貝塚市|12=draft}}, which were part of the historic pilgrimage route to {{ill|Kumano Sanzan|ja|熊野三山|12=draft}} along the {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft}}.
== Overview of Kujūku Ōji == {{Main|{{ill|Kujūku Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft}}}}
The Kujūku Ōji shrines refer to a group of sacred sites along the {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft}}, especially the {{ill|Kiiji|ja|紀伊路|1=Kiiji|12=draft}} route, established during the 12th and 13th centuries by {{ill|Kumano Shugendō|ja|熊野修験|12=draft}} practitioners. These shrines served to protect pilgrims, including members of the imperial family and nobility, on their journeys to the sacred sites of Kumano.
Following the decline of the {{ill|Kumano Pilgrimage|ja|熊野詣|12=draft}} after the {{ill|Jōkyū War|ja|承久の乱|12=draft}} in 1221, many of these shrines fell into disrepair. Despite some restoration efforts during the Edo period by the {{ill|Kishū Domain|ja|紀州藩|12=draft}}, many shrines were lost due to urbanization and the State Shinto reforms of the Meiji era.
This article focuses on the Kujūku Ōji shrines identified within Kishiwada and Kaizuka.
== Kujūku Ōji Shrines == There is one known Ōji shrine in Kishiwada and three in Kaizuka.
=== {{ill|Ikeda Ōji|ja|池田王子|12=draft}} === Located near {{ill|Kumeda Station|ja|久米田駅|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Hanwa Line|ja|阪和線|12=draft}}, the former site of Ikeda Ōji is now private land in Shimo-Ikeda, Kishiwada. The shrine was believed to be associated with {{ill|Sekigawa Shrine (Kishiwada|ja|積川神社|12=draft}} and was merged into {{ill|Yagi Shrine|ja|夜疑神社|12=draft}} during the Meiji period.
=== {{ill|Asokawa Ōji|ja|麻生川王子|12=draft}} === Also known as Aso River Ōji, it was merged into {{ill|Arimaku Shrine|ja|阿里莫神社|12=draft}} in Kaizuka in 1909. The shrine was venerated by the Handa community, and although its original location is now occupied by a factory, nearby landmarks commemorate its historical significance.
=== {{ill|Kuramochi Ōji|ja|鞍持王子|12=draft}} === Merged into {{ill|Minami Kogi Shrine|ja|南近義神社|12=draft}} in Kaizuka in 1907, the former shrine site still has a small torii gate and shrine structure. Some historical records suggest alternative locations, including near {{ill|Shōfuku-ji (Kaizuka|ja|正福寺|12=draft}}.
=== {{ill|Kogi Ōji|ja|近木王子|12=draft}} === Also known as Kogi Shin Ōji, it was merged into Minami Kogi Shrine in the late Meiji era. The former shrine site is debated, with possible locations near {{ill|Zenshō-ji (Kaizuka|ja|善正寺|12=draft}} or the former {{ill|Kumano Shrine (Kaizuka|ja|熊野神社|12=draft}} site.
== See Also == * {{ill|Kumano Sanzan|ja|熊野三山|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kumano Kōdō|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft}} - {{ill|Kiiji|ja|紀伊路|1=Kiiji|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft}} ''' {{ill|Inokuchi Ōji|ja|井ノ口王子|12=draft}} → '''{{ill|Yagi Shrine|ja|夜疑神社|fr|Yagi-jinja|lt=Ikeda Ōji|error=Kaizuka)|oji=王子|12=draft}}''' → '''{{ill|List of Kujūku Ōji (Kaizuka)|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=List of Kujūku Ōji (Kaizuka)|en|lt=Asokawa Ōji|error=九十九王子 (岸和田市・貝塚市)|oji=王子|12=draft}}''' → '''{{ill|List of Kujūku Ōji (Kaizuka)|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=List of Kujūku Ōji (Kaizuka)|en|lt=Kogi Ōji|error=九十九王子 (岸和田市・貝塚市)|oji=王子|12=draft}}''' → '''{{ill|List of Kujūku Ōji (Kaizuka)|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=List of Kujūku Ōji (Kaizuka)|en|lt=Kuramochi Ōji|error=九十九王子 (岸和田市・貝塚市)|oji=王子|12=draft}}''' → {{ill|List of Kujūku Ōji (Izumisano City)|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=List of Kujūku Ōji (Kaizuka)|en|lt=Tsuruhara Ōji|error=九十九王子 (岸和田市・貝塚市)|oji=王子|12=draft}}'''
