=== {{ill|List of Ninety-Nine Ōji (Kaizuka)|lt=List of Ninety-Nine Ōji (Kaizuka)|lt=Kogi Ōji|ja|近木王子|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kogi Ōji|qq=}} === Also known as Kogi Shin Ōji, it was merged into Minami Kogi Shrine in the late Meiji era. The former shrine site is debated, with possible locations near {{ill|Zenshō-ji (Kaizuka|ja|善正寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenshō-ji (Kaizuka|qq=}} or the former [[:en:Kumano shrine|Kumano Shrine (Kaizuka]] site.
